# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HassarPath | Scene: HassarPath
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The guards had said nothing to her. Sarah wondered if this was simply who they were, or if Hassar's threat had made them too afraid to speak."
    new "The guards had said nothing to her. Sarah wondered if this was simply who they were, or if Hassar's threat had made them too afraid to speak."

    old "He struck her as a man who did not tolerate disobedience."
    new "He struck her as a man who did not tolerate disobedience."

    old "From one hallway to the next, Sarah soon found herself arriving before a great ornate door, covered in gold and royal purple."
    new "From one hallway to the next, Sarah soon found herself arriving before a great ornate door, covered in gold and royal purple."

    old "As it opened, the guards pushed her through, and closed it behind her."
    new "As it opened, the guards pushed her through, and closed it behind her."

    old "She was alone and the hall was dark."
    new "She was alone and the hall was dark."

    old "Nowhere to go but forward, Sarah steeled her nerves and pressed on, slowly shuffling forward with only her touch to guide her."
    new "Nowhere to go but forward, Sarah steeled her nerves and pressed on, slowly shuffling forward with only her touch to guide her."

    old "In time, her eyes grew used to the darkness, and she could make out a few feet ahead of her."
    new "In time, her eyes grew used to the darkness, and she could make out a few feet ahead of her."

    old "The sanctum, that was what Hassar had called it, but Sarah had no idea what that would mean for her."
    new "The sanctum, that was what Hassar had called it, but Sarah had no idea what that would mean for her."

    old "From the distance, a voice rang out."
    new "From the distance, a voice rang out."

    old "Ooh! I think I hear a new girl! It's been a while!"
    new "Ooh! I think I hear a new girl! It's been a while!"

    old "The voice was high-pitched, unmistakably a woman's voice."
    new "The voice was high-pitched, unmistakably a woman's voice."

    old "Following the voice, Sarah moved down the hall."
    new "Following the voice, Sarah moved down the hall."

    old "As she suddenly turned a corner, the world opened up before her."
    new "As she suddenly turned a corner, the world opened up before her."

    old "Sarah raised her hands to cover her eyes from the sudden light."
    new "Sarah raised her hands to cover her eyes from the sudden light."

    old "For a moment, she saw but her mind struggled to make sense of it."
    new "For a moment, she saw but her mind struggled to make sense of it."

    old "She had expected any manner of things, but this place was not one of them."
    new "She had expected any manner of things, but this place was not one of them."

    old "Slowly, Sarah began to make sense of it all."
    new "Slowly, Sarah began to make sense of it all."

    old "An elaborate bathhouse seemed to have been constructed on the inside of the palace."
    new "An elaborate bathhouse seemed to have been constructed on the inside of the palace."

    old "Sarah assumed she was still in the palace, but at the same time it felt somehow different. Seperate from the rest of the building."
    new "Sarah assumed she was still in the palace, but at the same time it felt somehow different. Seperate from the rest of the building."

    old "Here there was no noise of the countless visitors and dignitaries buzzing about."
    new "Here there was no noise of the countless visitors and dignitaries buzzing about."

    old "Here there was only a soft and calm space."
    new "Here there was only a soft and calm space."

    old "Soothing, in ever sense, Sarah realized."
    new "Soothing, in ever sense, Sarah realized."

    old "The air felt more humid, softly caressing her skin as droplets of water formed."
    new "The air felt more humid, softly caressing her skin as droplets of water formed."

    old "Scented spices filled her nose with the smell of fruit."
    new "Scented spices filled her nose with the smell of fruit."

    old "Even the temperature was cool and relaxing to the touch, where in the palace itself the heat had been opressive."
    new "Even the temperature was cool and relaxing to the touch, where in the palace itself the heat had been opressive."

    old "Sarah took a few steps forward."
    new "Sarah took a few steps forward."

    old "In front of her, she saw the clear blue waters, gently pouring forth from a source she could not yet find."
    new "In front of her, she saw the clear blue waters, gently pouring forth from a source she could not yet find."

    old "Suddenly, to her left, Sarah noticed a movement from the corner of her eyes."
    new "Suddenly, to her left, Sarah noticed a movement from the corner of her eyes."

    old "The girl's high-pitched voice and screaming made Sarah's ears ring."
    new "The girl's high-pitched voice and screaming made Sarah's ears ring."

    old "Sarah instantly noticed how little the girl was wearing, but at the same time, she realized she wasn't wearing much herself."
    new "Sarah instantly noticed how little the girl was wearing, but at the same time, she realized she wasn't wearing much herself."

    old "You're really here! A new arrival!"
    new "You're really here! A new arrival!"

    old "Who are you? What's going on?"
    new "Who are you? What's going on?"

    old "The girl rushed forward, throwing her arms around Sarah in an embrace."
    new "The girl rushed forward, throwing her arms around Sarah in an embrace."

    old "Sarah felt her warm, naked body press up against her own."
    new "Sarah felt her warm, naked body press up against her own."

    old "Unsure of what else to do, she reluctanctly returned the greeting."
    new "Unsure of what else to do, she reluctanctly returned the greeting."

    old "Backing away from her, Sarah saw the girl's wide smile."
    new "Backing away from her, Sarah saw the girl's wide smile."

    old "I'm Sophia, nice to meet you!"
    new "I'm Sophia, nice to meet you!"

    old "What's your name?"
    new "What's your name?"

    old "Only just earlier this day, she had been brought here as a slave, humbled before the man that conquered her nation..."
    new "Only just earlier this day, she had been brought here as a slave, humbled before the man that conquered her nation..."

    old "And now she was in this strange place, faced with this strange girl."
    new "And now she was in this strange place, faced with this strange girl."

    old "My name is Sarah..."
    new "My name is Sarah..."

    old "Ooh, Sarah! That's a pretty name."
    new "Ooh, Sarah! That's a pretty name."

    old "I...thank you."
    new "I...thank you."

    old "Sarah wasn't sure what else to say."
    new "Sarah wasn't sure what else to say."

    old "Can you tell me...where I am?"
    new "Can you tell me...where I am?"

    old "The girl nodded, seemingly eager for a chance to explain."
    new "The girl nodded, seemingly eager for a chance to explain."

    old "This is the sanctum."
    new "This is the sanctum."

    old "Are we still in the palace?"
    new "Are we still in the palace?"

    old "The girl nodded again."
    new "The girl nodded again."

    old "Yeah, the sanctum is Hassar's private retreat from the rest of the world."
    new "Yeah, the sanctum is Hassar's private retreat from the rest of the world."

    old "His life is very taxing. Many meetings, sometimes he even rides out to war."
    new "His life is very taxing. Many meetings, sometimes he even rides out to war."

    old "The girl seemed to almost look sad as she said it."
    new "The girl seemed to almost look sad as she said it."

    old "So this is a place for him to get away from all that. A chance to relax, and let all the awful stuff out there, slip away."
    new "So this is a place for him to get away from all that. A chance to relax, and let all the awful stuff out there, slip away."

    old "The girl smiled."
    new "The girl smiled."

    old "These are his private quarters?"
    new "These are his private quarters?"

    old "But nobody is allowed in here."
    new "But nobody is allowed in here."

    old "Sarah studied the girl, but she appeared entirely untroubled by all of this."
    new "Sarah studied the girl, but she appeared entirely untroubled by all of this."

    old "Except for you and me."
    new "Except for you and me."

    old "You, me, and the others of course."
    new "You, me, and the others of course."

    old "The others?"
    new "The others?"

    old "The girl turned her head and looked around."
    new "The girl turned her head and looked around."

    old "Yeah...I don't see them yet, but the should be around here somewhere."
    new "Yeah...I don't see them yet, but the should be around here somewhere."

    old "It's a pretty big place."
    new "It's a pretty big place."

    old "She laughed."
    new "She laughed."

    old "Who...who are the others, exactly?"
    new "Who...who are the others, exactly?"

    old "The other members of the harem, you'll meet them soon enough."
    new "The other members of the harem, you'll meet them soon enough."

    old "Harem."
    new "Harem."

    old "The word struck her like a hammer."
    new "The word struck her like a hammer."

    old "What...what do you mean, harem?"
    new "What...what do you mean, harem?"

    old "The girl looked at Sarah with a puzzled expression, as if confused that she'd even asked."
    new "The girl looked at Sarah with a puzzled expression, as if confused that she'd even asked."

    old "Well...Hassar comes here to relax and it's our job to help him relax, in any way we can."
    new "Well...Hassar comes here to relax and it's our job to help him relax, in any way we can."

    old "Sarah felt her heart sink."
    new "Sarah felt her heart sink."

    old "You mean he's going to rape me?!"
    new "You mean he's going to rape me?!"

    old "Sarah saw the girl's eyes go wide. She began to shake her head."
    new "Sarah saw the girl's eyes go wide. She began to shake her head."

    old "Ooh no! Not at all!"
    new "Ooh no! Not at all!"

    old "Sarah suddenly grew confused again."
    new "Sarah suddenly grew confused again."

    old "I thought you meant he...had sex with you."
    new "I thought you meant he...had sex with you."

    old "Yeah, he does. With all of us. But it's not like...what you said!"
    new "Yeah, he does. With all of us. But it's not like...what you said!"

    old "We do it because we want to. Because he's our Khan. And he provides for all of us, really."
    new "We do it because we want to. Because he's our Khan. And he provides for all of us, really."

    old "Sarah didn't know much about the world of the tribesmen, but she doubted that she had much rights to refuse Hassar if he forced herself on her."
    new "Sarah didn't know much about the world of the tribesmen, but she doubted that she had much rights to refuse Hassar if he forced herself on her."

    old "He didn't force himself on you?"
    new "He didn't force himself on you?"

    old "No, never!"
    new "No, never!"

    old "I mean...when I first came here, I was scared, and I think I had some of the same fears as you had."
    new "I mean...when I first came here, I was scared, and I think I had some of the same fears as you had."

    old "But on the first night, Hassar came to me and he told me he'd never do anything I didn't want to do."
    new "But on the first night, Hassar came to me and he told me he'd never do anything I didn't want to do."

    old "Instead, he only asked me if there was anything he could do for me to make my stay here more comfortable."
    new "Instead, he only asked me if there was anything he could do for me to make my stay here more comfortable."

    old "The girl laughed."
    new "The girl laughed."

    old "So I told him I wanted a picture book from Lethram, the kind I had when I was growing up."
    new "So I told him I wanted a picture book from Lethram, the kind I had when I was growing up."

    old "And I swear, in only a few days, he had it here for me!"
    new "And I swear, in only a few days, he had it here for me!"

    old "The girl was smiling as she told her story."
    new "The girl was smiling as she told her story."

    old "Then I got my own room, and more stuff, and he never did anything. He was so nice!"
    new "Then I got my own room, and more stuff, and he never did anything. He was so nice!"

    old "We walked around the gardens a bit, and he told me all about his life and...well, I kind of just...fell in love with him."
    new "We walked around the gardens a bit, and he told me all about his life and...well, I kind of just...fell in love with him."

    old "He's not at all as mean as people think he is. He's actually a big softie under it all."
    new "He's not at all as mean as people think he is. He's actually a big softie under it all."

    old "Sarah listened with utter disbelief at Sophia's story."
    new "Sarah listened with utter disbelief at Sophia's story."

    old "The Khan, the man that broke her nation and made her people slaves, had made her a slave..."
    new "The Khan, the man that broke her nation and made her people slaves, had made her a slave..."

    old "Was supposedly nice?"
    new "Was supposedly nice?"

    old "No, that's not possible..."
    new "No, that's not possible..."

    old "The girl shrugged."
    new "The girl shrugged."

    old "You'll see. I'm sure he'll come by soon enough, and I promise he won't even lay a finger on you. He's really not the person you think he is."
    new "You'll see. I'm sure he'll come by soon enough, and I promise he won't even lay a finger on you. He's really not the person you think he is."

    old "Sarah took a step forward."
    new "Sarah took a step forward."

    old "He conquered my people!"
    new "He conquered my people!"

    old "Well...he is the Khan, after all."
    new "Well...he is the Khan, after all."

    old "That...that doesn't justify any of it!"
    new "That...that doesn't justify any of it!"

    old "The girl shrugged again."
    new "The girl shrugged again."

    old "Look, a lot of people here in Al'Gahaem have it a lot worse than those of us in the harem."
    new "Look, a lot of people here in Al'Gahaem have it a lot worse than those of us in the harem."

    old "You should feel lucky that he likes you enough to invite you here."
    new "You should feel lucky that he likes you enough to invite you here."

    old "I'm sure after a while, you'll learn to see how different he is!"
    new "I'm sure after a while, you'll learn to see how different he is!"

    old "Sarah struggled to find the words to respond, but before she even could, she saw another figure approached."
    new "Sarah struggled to find the words to respond, but before she even could, she saw another figure approached."

    old "Sophia, why are you making a racket?"
    new "Sophia, why are you making a racket?"

    old "Sarah saw the woman approach, a bit older but not by much, she was as scantily clad as the both of them."
    new "Sarah saw the woman approach, a bit older but not by much, she was as scantily clad as the both of them."

    old "Whatever it was, the woman seemed entirely unbothered by her own nakedness, walking in a confident manner."
    new "Whatever it was, the woman seemed entirely unbothered by her own nakedness, walking in a confident manner."

    old "Ooh, a visitor?"
    new "Ooh, a visitor?"

    old "Sarah watched the woman look at her, her eyes gliding across Sarah's body as though studying it."
    new "Sarah watched the woman look at her, her eyes gliding across Sarah's body as though studying it."

    old "I can see why he'd like you."
    new "I can see why he'd like you."

    old "The woman smiled."
    new "The woman smiled."

    old "I'm Sarah."
    new "I'm Sarah."

    old "It was all she could manage in this strange place."
    new "It was all she could manage in this strange place."

    old "Sarah...that's a lovely name."
    new "Sarah...that's a lovely name."

    old "My name is Naydeen, pleasure to meet you."
    new "My name is Naydeen, pleasure to meet you."

    old "I hope Sophia here wasn't talking your ears off."
    new "I hope Sophia here wasn't talking your ears off."

    old "Hey! I don't do that!"
    new "Hey! I don't do that!"

    old "The woman patted Sophia on the shoulder, as if to calm her down."
    new "The woman patted Sophia on the shoulder, as if to calm her down."

    old "Don't worry, Sophia, without you this place would be a bore."
    new "Don't worry, Sophia, without you this place would be a bore."

    old "Sophia started to smile, seemingly placated by the compliment."
    new "Sophia started to smile, seemingly placated by the compliment."

    old "Anyway, Sarah was it? Come with me, I'll take you to your room."
    new "Anyway, Sarah was it? Come with me, I'll take you to your room."

    old "My room?"
    new "My room?"

    old "The woman nodded."
    new "The woman nodded."

    old "Everyone here has a private quarters where they can retreat if they want to be alone."
    new "Everyone here has a private quarters where they can retreat if they want to be alone."

    old "And sometimes where Hassar can visit if he only wants to speak to one of us."
    new "And sometimes where Hassar can visit if he only wants to speak to one of us."

    old "The woman emphasised the word speak, as if to suggest that was hardly all she meant by it."
    new "The woman emphasised the word speak, as if to suggest that was hardly all she meant by it."

    old "Sarah felt the woman link her arm through hers and begin to pull her away."
    new "Sarah felt the woman link her arm through hers and begin to pull her away."

    old "Be a dear, Sophia, and gather some warm water for our friend so she can bathe herself, I think she's been through an awful lot."
    new "Be a dear, Sophia, and gather some warm water for our friend so she can bathe herself, I think she's been through an awful lot."

    old "Sarah watched as Sophia ran away, excitedly, to take to her task."
    new "Sarah watched as Sophia ran away, excitedly, to take to her task."

    old "Whatever it was, Naydeen seemed to exert some degree of natural authority here."
    new "Whatever it was, Naydeen seemed to exert some degree of natural authority here."

    old "Sarah allowed herself to be guided alone, there wasn't much else she could do."
    new "Sarah allowed herself to be guided alone, there wasn't much else she could do."

    old "I imagine the girl's talked a whole lot without saying much."
    new "I imagine the girl's talked a whole lot without saying much."

    old "Yeah, I'm still confused about this place..."
    new "Yeah, I'm still confused about this place..."

    old "That's fine, it took quite a while for all of us to settle here, but in time we made it work."
    new "That's fine, it took quite a while for all of us to settle here, but in time we made it work."

    old "So this is...the Khan's private harem?"
    new "So this is...the Khan's private harem?"

    old "Naydeen nodded."
    new "Naydeen nodded."

    old "Yes, this is his sanctum, where we are kept safe and away from the rest of the city. The world, really."
    new "Yes, this is his sanctum, where we are kept safe and away from the rest of the city. The world, really."

    old "But don't think of it like a prison."
    new "But don't think of it like a prison."

    old "There is nothing you want that you can't get, all you need to do is ask for it and they'll deliver it as soon as they can."
    new "There is nothing you want that you can't get, all you need to do is ask for it and they'll deliver it as soon as they can."

    old "If it's in the city, you'll likely get it the same day. Other items can take a while, but Hassar has always come through on any request."
    new "If it's in the city, you'll likely get it the same day. Other items can take a while, but Hassar has always come through on any request."

    old "But I don't understand...he's a conquerer...he destroyed my country."
    new "But I don't understand...he's a conquerer...he destroyed my country."

    old "The woman seemed quiet for a moment."
    new "The woman seemed quiet for a moment."

    old "And that's awful."
    new "And that's awful."

    old "But it's the way of the world, I'm afraid."
    new "But it's the way of the world, I'm afraid."

    old "Strength dictates all, and Hassar is the strongest man I've ever met."
    new "Strength dictates all, and Hassar is the strongest man I've ever met."

    old "Yours is not the first nation he broke and I suspect it won't be the last."
    new "Yours is not the first nation he broke and I suspect it won't be the last."

    old "Tell me...was it Rosanna?"
    new "Tell me...was it Rosanna?"

    old "We are isolated here, but we are not in a prison. Whispers, rumors, they make their way even inside this place."
    new "We are isolated here, but we are not in a prison. Whispers, rumors, they make their way even inside this place."

    old "I had heard that the campaign against your country had begun. I had not yet heard how it was going."
    new "I had heard that the campaign against your country had begun. I had not yet heard how it was going."

    old "But suspecting you're here, I imagine it went quite well...for the tribesmen."
    new "But suspecting you're here, I imagine it went quite well...for the tribesmen."

    old "Yes...our armies were crushed, our capital sacked...I..."
    new "Yes...our armies were crushed, our capital sacked...I..."

    old "The woman observed Sarah again as they continued to walk down the halls."
    new "The woman observed Sarah again as they continued to walk down the halls."

    old "Let me guess, you were a noble lady?"
    new "Let me guess, you were a noble lady?"

    old "Sarah slowly nodded her head."
    new "Sarah slowly nodded her head."

    old "I was the princess of Rosanna..."
    new "I was the princess of Rosanna..."

    old "Your body. It's soft and unblemished. No commoner would have gotten to your age without some scars or muscle."
    new "Your body. It's soft and unblemished. No commoner would have gotten to your age without some scars or muscle."

    old "Ooh...I never knew it was that obvious..."
    new "Ooh...I never knew it was that obvious..."

    old "I understand that you must find this new situation quite confusing, but I promise you that there is something to be happy about."
    new "I understand that you must find this new situation quite confusing, but I promise you that there is something to be happy about."

    old "Happy? In this place?"
    new "Happy? In this place?"

    old "You will be provided for here. The Khan is a strong and powerful man."
    new "You will be provided for here. The Khan is a strong and powerful man."

    old "We live under his protection, but he values us for what we can offer him return. A softness. A gentleness."
    new "We live under his protection, but he values us for what we can offer him return. A softness. A gentleness."

    old "Sarah faced Naydeen."
    new "Sarah faced Naydeen."

    old "Sex...you mean."
    new "Sex...you mean."

    old "Naydeen shrugged."
    new "Naydeen shrugged."

    old "I won't lie and say that's not part of it."
    new "I won't lie and say that's not part of it."

    old "But he listens to us, speaks to us as people. He is not as brutish as he appears to the outside world."
    new "But he listens to us, speaks to us as people. He is not as brutish as he appears to the outside world."

    old "And as for the sex, he cares for our pleasures as much as his own, a rare trait in this place."
    new "And as for the sex, he cares for our pleasures as much as his own, a rare trait in this place."

    old "Naydeen looked into Sarah's eyes."
    new "Naydeen looked into Sarah's eyes."

    old "What do you know of such things, anyway?"
    new "What do you know of such things, anyway?"

    old "Didn't your mother ever tell you anything of such things?"
    new "Didn't your mother ever tell you anything of such things?"

    old "Sarah shook her head, still red in the face."
    new "Sarah shook her head, still red in the face."

    old "Naydeen laughed."
    new "Naydeen laughed."

    old "Khan Hassar is gentle."
    new "Khan Hassar is gentle."

    old "Sophia said he...would not force me."
    new "Sophia said he...would not force me."

    old "There are four girls here, five with you now."
    new "There are four girls here, five with you now."

    old "He has never forced himself on any of us."
    new "He has never forced himself on any of us."

    old "Not in the beginning, not ever since."
    new "Not in the beginning, not ever since."

    old "Each of us gave ourselves willing to him in time, when we came to see him for the man he was."
    new "Each of us gave ourselves willing to him in time, when we came to see him for the man he was."

    old "But he could...couldn't he?"
    new "But he could...couldn't he?"

    old "Physically? By right? Of course, but he is simply no such man."
    new "Physically? By right? Of course, but he is simply no such man."

    old "He can have thousands of women brought before him, each eager to serve him."
    new "He can have thousands of women brought before him, each eager to serve him."

    old "What need would he have to force himself on a girl?"
    new "What need would he have to force himself on a girl?"

    old "And why would such a man, who can have a girl willingly, otherwise take one by force?"
    new "And why would such a man, who can have a girl willingly, otherwise take one by force?"

    old "Sarah was quiet as she pondered it. She had not thought about it like that before."
    new "Sarah was quiet as she pondered it. She had not thought about it like that before."

    old "So...he won't..."
    new "So...he won't..."

    old "The woman shook her head."
    new "The woman shook her head."

    old "No more than you yourself want."
    new "No more than you yourself want."

    old "She leaned in close and whispered to Sarah."
    new "She leaned in close and whispered to Sarah."

    old "But you will find him tempting, in time, and if you have had him, ooh trust me, you'll curse yourself for every day you wasted denying him."
    new "But you will find him tempting, in time, and if you have had him, ooh trust me, you'll curse yourself for every day you wasted denying him."

    old "Sarah felt herself turn redder still."
    new "Sarah felt herself turn redder still."

    old "Suddenly they turned a corner and a room opened up before them."
    new "Suddenly they turned a corner and a room opened up before them."

    old "Draped and decorated in the style of the tribes, Sarah felt her eyes lost in the splendor of it."
    new "Draped and decorated in the style of the tribes, Sarah felt her eyes lost in the splendor of it."

    old "Everywhere, beautiful colored silk drowned the room in a bright hue."
    new "Everywhere, beautiful colored silk drowned the room in a bright hue."

    old "Gold and jewels glittered, casually strewn across the room."
    new "Gold and jewels glittered, casually strewn across the room."

    old "Sarah felt her jaw fall open."
    new "Sarah felt her jaw fall open."

    old "It's..."
    new "It's..."

    old "It was more extravagant than even her room back in Castle Reinmeer."
    new "It was more extravagant than even her room back in Castle Reinmeer."

    old "The woman laughed."
    new "The woman laughed."

    old "Yes, it took my breath away the first time too."
    new "Yes, it took my breath away the first time too."

    old "But don't worry, this is just how the room is now."
    new "But don't worry, this is just how the room is now."

    old "It's all yours, you can let it be adjusted to whatever style you like."
    new "It's all yours, you can let it be adjusted to whatever style you like."

    old "I think Ayaka had her room redone in the style of the eastern kingdoms, reminds her of home she says."
    new "I think Ayaka had her room redone in the style of the eastern kingdoms, reminds her of home she says."

    old "Ayaka?"
    new "Ayaka?"

    old "Ooh, one of the other girls, you'll meet her soon enough I imagine."
    new "Ooh, one of the other girls, you'll meet her soon enough I imagine."

    old "I'll let you stay here to get comfortable. Sophia will be here shortly with some warm water to clean yourself."
    new "I'll let you stay here to get comfortable. Sophia will be here shortly with some warm water to clean yourself."

    old "Sarah felt Naydeen grab her wrist and pull her."
    new "Sarah felt Naydeen grab her wrist and pull her."

    old "Sarah, I understand you have your reservations. It is only natural."
    new "Sarah, I understand you have your reservations. It is only natural."

    old "But the Khan...he is our master, and he demands and is entitled to a certain degree of respect."
